Due to a lack of avilability our standard rooms, we were upgraded to a JUNIOR SUITE for the same price we paid for the standard room.	If you book one of the "standard rooms" which we did as it was the only room left, be sure to ask the reservation agent about the views from the windows.	Seems to me this would be standard business practice given the large deposit and amended cancellation policy.	We stayed many times before at this high-reputation hotel, but returning this Feb with friends we found that the mid-range price was now extended to the cheaper rooms.	We stayed in a poolside standard room on the second level.